        <h1>Comprehensive File Format Support</h1>

        <p>SeqR supports the full range of standard genomic file formats:</p>

        <h3>Primary annotation formats:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>BED files</strong> - Browser Extensible Data for genomic intervals</li>
            <li><strong>GFF3/GFF2/GFF</strong> - Gene Feature Format for detailed annotations</li>
            <li><strong>GTF</strong> - Gene Transfer Format for gene and transcript models</li>
            <li><strong>FASTA</strong> - Reference sequence data</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Exotic formats:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>VCF</strong> - Variant Call Format for genetic variations</li>
            <li><strong>BEDGRAPH</strong> - Coverage and signal tracks</li>
            <li><strong>WIG</strong> - Wiggle format for continuous data</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Automatic format detection streamlines the data import process.</p>
    </div>

